race.comment: SKETCH (8) looks the one to beat. Two runs back this time in have been very good, narrowly beaten at Kilmore fresh before starting $2.20 favourite at Ballarat when third to Strictly Business, who won the G1 VRC Oaks just 13 days later. Out to a mile from the inside draw can see her settle closer and from there she should be too good. FALSTAFFIAN (4) has been solid in two runs to date, finishing fifth on each occasion. The debut at Sandown Hillside was in a good race before boxing on late at Sale. He should take running down. SKY DEEL (5) made good improvement second up out to this trip at Cranbourne when finding a progressive one a bit too strong. Fitter again now and should be right there. RACEY CASEY (7) is knocking on the door with consecutive minor placings. She should be knocking one off soon.
